# Git workflow — Beantol bot

## Commits and pushes

- **Ask the user before every commit and push** unless they explicitly approve in the current message (e.g. "commit and push").
- Do not commit `.env` or secrets.

## `last-working-bot` tag (rollback bookmark)

- **Do NOT move or create `last-working-bot`** as part of routine commits or pushes.
- **Only update `last-working-bot`** when the user **explicitly** asks (e.g. "mark as last working bot", "update last-working-bot").
- When updating: `git tag -f last-working-bot HEAD` then `git push -f origin last-working-bot` (only if user also asked to push the tag).
- Current bookmark (as of user request): `dc37505` — docs + full bot through appointment/handoff/Cebu delivery work.

## Revert reference for user

To restore the bookmark locally: `git reset --hard last-working-bot`
